              java.util.Date newDate,

        Parameters:

        timeout - the time (in milliseconds) that can pass since last ping before the device is considered to have timed out
        newDate - the time of the most recent ping from the device
        address - the IP Address of the device

      • RPICam

        public RPICam(java.lang.String constructString,
              int code)
        Constructor to create a new instance of RPICam using a String that contains the ID, the Location, and potentially the IPAddress if the device is online, all separated by a '%' symbol. Also takes a code to indicate whether the device is online (and therefore if the constructString contains an IPAddress parameter).
        Parameters:
        constructString - the String that contains details to parse
        code - integer, 1 indicates online device that has an IP Address, 0 indicated offline with no IP Adress
